"Bender M.A., Knutson T.R., Tuleya R.E., Sirutis J.J., Vecchi G.A., Garner S.T., Held I.M.","Modeled impact of anthropogenic warming on the frequency of intense Atlantic hurricanes",2010,"Science","327","5964",,"454","458",,,10.1126/science.1180568,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-75749084428&partnerID=40&md5=ac4afd9d8c1ab0cacaf4573cf9470970","National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration/Geophysical Fluid Dynamics Laboratory, 201 Forrestal Road, Princeton, NJ, 08540, United States; Center for Coastal Physical Oceanography, Old Dominion University, 4111 Monarch Way, Norfolk, VA 23508, United States","Bender, M.A., National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration/Geophysical Fluid Dynamics Laboratory, 201 Forrestal Road, Princeton, NJ, 08540, United States; Knutson, T.R., National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration/Geophysical Fluid Dynamics Laboratory, 201 Forrestal Road, Princeton, NJ, 08540, United States; Tuleya, R.E., Center for Coastal Physical Oceanography, Old Dominion University, 4111 Monarch Way, Norfolk, VA 23508, United States; Sirutis, J.J., National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration/Geophysical Fluid Dynamics Laboratory, 201 Forrestal Road, Princeton, NJ, 08540, United States; Vecchi, G.A., National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration/Geophysical Fluid Dynamics Laboratory, 201 Forrestal Road, Princeton, NJ, 08540, United States; Garner, S.T., National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration/Geophysical Fluid Dynamics Laboratory, 201 Forrestal Road, Princeton, NJ, 08540, United States; Held, I.M., National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration/Geophysical Fluid Dynamics Laboratory, 201 Forrestal Road, Princeton, NJ, 08540, United States","Several recent models suggest that the frequency of Atlantic tropical cyclones could decrease as the climate warms. However, these models are unable to reproduce storms of category 3 or higher intensity. We explored the influence of future global warming on Atlantic hurricanes with a downscaling strategy by using an operational hurricane-prediction model that produces a realistic distribution of intense hurricane activity for present-day conditions. The model projects nearly a doubling of the frequency of category 4 and 5 storms by the end of the 21st century, despite a decrease in the overall frequency of tropical cyclones, when the downscaling is based on the ensemble mean of 18 global climate-change projections. The largest increase is projected to occur in the Western Atlantic, north of 20°N.",,"anthropogenic effect; climate modeling; downscaling; ensemble forecasting; global warming; hurricane; twenty first century; article; Atlantic islands; climate; climate change; greenhouse effect; hurricane; priority journal; sea surface temperature; Atlantic Ocean; Atlantic Ocean (West)",,,,,,"(2007) Climate Change 2007: the Physical Science Basis. Contribution of Working Group i to the Fourth Assessment Report of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change, , S. Solomon et al., Eds., Cambridge Univ. Press, Cambridge; Santer, B.D., (2006) Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A., 103, p. 13905; Gillett, N.P., Stott, P.A., Santer, B.D., (2008) Geophys. Res. Lett., 35, pp. L09707; Zhang, R., Delworth, T.L., (2006) Geophys. Res. Lett., 33, pp. L17712; Evan, A.T., Vimont, D.J., Heidinger, A.K., Kossin, J.P., Bennartz, R., (2009) Science, 324, p. 778; Mann, M., Emanuel, K., (2006) Eos, 87, p. 233; Eisner, J.B., Kossin, J.P., Jagger, T.H., (2008) Nature, 455, p. 92; Emanuel, K.A., (2005) Nature, 436, p. 686; Knutson, T.R., Sirutis, J.J., Garner, S.T., Vecchi, G.A., Held, I.M., (2008) Nat. Geosci., 1, p. 359; Zhao, M., Held, I.M., Lin, S.J., Vecchi, G.A., (2009) J. Clim., 22, p. 6653; Vecchi, G.A., Swanson, K.L., Soden, B.J., (2008) Science, 322, p. 687; Holland, G.J., Webster, P.J., (2007) Philos. Trans. R. Soc., 365, p. 2695; Vecchi, G.A., Knutson, T.R., (2008) J. Clim., 21, p. 3580; Bengtsson, L.K., (2007) Tellus, 59 A, p. 539; Gualdi, S., Scoccimarro, E., Navarra, A., (2008) J. Clim., 21, p. 5204; Knutson, T.R., Sirutis, J.J., Garner, S.T., Held, I.M., Tuleya, R.E., (2007) Bull. Am. Meteorol. Soc., 88, p. 1549; Meehl, G.A., (2007) Bull. Am. Meteorol. Soc., 88, p. 1383; Bender, M.A., Ginis, I., Tuleya, R.E., Thomas, B., Marchok, T., (2007) Mon. Weather Rev., 135, p. 3965; Bender, M.A., Ginis, I., (2000) Mon. Weather Rev., 128, p. 917; Vecchi, G.A., Soden, B.J., (2007) Geophys. Res. Lett., 34, pp. L08702; Pielke, R.A., (2008) Nat. Hazards Rev., 9, p. 29; Emanuel, K., (2007) J. Clim., 20, p. 5497; note","Bender, M. A.; National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration/Geophysical Fluid Dynamics Laboratory, 201 Forrestal Road, Princeton, NJ, 08540, United States; email: Morris.Bender@noaa.gov",,,,,,,,00368075,,SCIEA,,"English","Science",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-75749084428
